caption.body: Cheju or Jeju Island, located 50 miles off the southern peninsula of South Korea, is Korea's largest island. Seongsan Ilchulbong, a volcanic crater, pictured here, is considered one of Korea's most beautiful natural wonders. Featuring a breathtaking panoramic view of the Jeju Island, Hallasan Mountain and the surrounding ocean, millions of visitors climb to the top of the crater every year. Hallasan Mountain is the tallest peak in South Korea.
